&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integration meets Innovation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Celigo, we believe integration should empower — not exhaust — innovation. As a modern Integration and Automation Platform (iPaaS), we’re on a mission to simplify how companies integrate, automate, and optimize processes. Powered by game-changing technology like runtime AI and prebuilt, mission-critical integrations, Celigo is redefining how businesses connect their world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Celigo is looking for a&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Software Architect&lt;/strong&gt; to help own and evolve the CloudExtend product portfolio. This is a hands-on individual contributor role responsible for the reliability, security, scalability, and operation of our SaaS platforms, while providing architectural direction and technical guidance across engineering teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for maintaining and improving existing production systems, supporting critical customer escalations, leading security and compliance initiatives, driving platform modernisation efforts, and evaluating emerging technologies that improve engineering effectiveness and product capabilities. While the role includes architecture and design responsibilities, success in this position requires strong operational ownership and the ability to effectively run large-scale SaaS platforms in production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong software engineering fundamentals with deep AWS expertise, experience operating enterprise SaaS products at scale, and a passion for adopting modern engineering practices including AI-assisted development and platform automation.&lt;/p&gt;
