&lt;li&gt;Architect and design scalable, secure, and performant cloud-native applications and platform services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the design and delivery of features by collaborating with engineering, product, support, and cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take critical architectural decisions that balance scalability, maintainability, security, reliability, and cost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute hands-on to the codebase and establish engineering best practices across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and develop frameworks, proofs of concept, and reusable platform capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead architecture, design, and technical review discussions across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and enforce architectural standards, patterns, and engineering best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify scalability, reliability, security, and operational risks and drive mitigation strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and manage a technical debt strategy and drive platform modernisation initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure production systems are operating efficiently, securely, and cost effectively while continuously identifying opportunities for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own architecture and governance across AWS infrastructure, networking, security, and platform services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and support SaaS platform capabilities including tenant management, licensing, subscriptions, entitlement models, and platform migrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technical aspects of security and compliance initiatives including SOC2 audits, penetration testing, vulnerability remediation, customer security reviews, and security questionnaires.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to security incidents, production issues, and critical customer escalations while driving root cause analysis and corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Support, Product, Engineering, and Customer Success teams to resolve complex customer issues and platform escalations.&lt;/li&gt;
